2. Full Architecture Overview – Enclave / Sandbox / Live Deployment
High-level layers (top-down)
Live Deployment
    ↑ (OTA / sideloading)
Sandbox (User-space, debug, hot-reload)
    ↑ (strict policy enforcement)
Secure Enclave (Hardware root – keys, wake word model, boot attestation)
    ↓ (isolated execution)
Hardware: Mic + CPU + Secure Boot
Sequence Diagram (text version – install → first wake)
User → Phone: Install app / run script
Phone → Enclave: Request key derivation + model load
Enclave → Phone: Return encrypted session key (only if attested)
Phone → Sandbox: Start listener daemon
Sandbox → Enclave: Send audio chunk (encrypted)
Enclave → Sandbox: Wake word match? (yes → decrypt command)
Sandbox → System: Execute command (open files, etc.)
User ← Phone: Visual feedback / voice response
